        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 4:47PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nappanee, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Nappanee, Syracuse, Milford, Leesburg, Clunette, Gravelton, Dewart
Lake, Hastings, Oakwood Park, and Monoquet.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
